🎥 Title

Forgot MySQL Workbench Password? Reset MySQL Root Password in 5 Minutes | 100% Working

📝 Video Flow
1. Hook (0:00–0:20)

"Forgot your MySQL Workbench password? Don't reinstall MySQL! I'll show you how to reset it in just 5 minutes."

2. Clarify the Problem (0:20–0:40)
MySQL Workbench doesn't have its own password.
It uses the MySQL Server (root) password.
3. Stop MySQL Service
net stop MySQL80
4. Start MySQL in Recovery Mode
mysqld --defaults-file="C:\ProgramData\MySQL\MySQL Server 8.0\my.ini" --skip-grant-tables --shared-memory
5. Login Without Password
mysql -u root
6. Reset Password
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost'
IDENTIFIED BY 'NewPassword123';

FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
7. Restart MySQL Service
net start MySQL80
8. Test Login
mysql -u root -p

Enter your new password.

9. Open MySQL Workbench
Connect using the new password.
Save it in the password vault if prompted.
🎯 Common Errors
mysql is not recognized → Navigate to the bin folder.
Access denied → Wrong password.
Server Stopped → Start the MySQL service.
Data directory not found → Use the correct my.ini.
